{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_kestrel_ver01/data/sn85060004/00516994757/1937113001/1022.xml":{"full_text":"NOVEMBER 30, 1937.\n1-[EAR TERW\nIN DOPE CASE\nFirst conviction in Bexar county\nunder the new state narcotic law\nwas made Tuesday when F. Davila,\naddress given at 246 San Luis street,\nwas sentenced to two years in the\npenitentiary for possession of mari\nhuana.\nDavila was charged with having\none of the drugged cigarettes on Oc\ntober 30 in a complain signed by R.\nE. Harkrider, an agent in the nar\ncotic division of the state depart\nment of public safety.\nUnder the new law the minimum\nsentence is two years. Suspended\nsentences cannot be given, Hark\nrider said. Before the new law was\npassed, a light fine or 30 days in the\ncounty jail could be assessed. _\n\nBusiness Recession\nMisses Southwest\nThe United States\u2019 much vaunted\nbusiness recession is conspicuous by\nits absence in Texas and the Far\nWest, according to Thomas Gore,\nMexico City hotel operator,\nGore and his wife were stopping\nat the St. Anthony hotel Tuesday en\nroute home after a two-months va\ncation in California. They are trav\neling by motor and will leave Wed\nnesday for the Mexico capital, where\nGore is president of the Geneve Ho-\ntel company.\n\u00abAll the way from the Mexican\nborder to Southern California I saw\nconcrete evidence of general pros\nperity,\u201d the hotel executive said. \u201cIf\nthere has been a recession I saw no\nevidence of it.\u201d\nGore did see the start of one re\ncession. It was in Elysian park, Los\nAngeles, where the side of a moun\ntain had just begun to slip down on\nRiverside drive. After he left Cali\nfornia a million-ton section of the\nmountain did slide down.\nO\n2.DROP\u201d TREATMENT\nJust put 2 drops of Penetro Nose\nDrops in each nostril and get relief\nfrom the discomfort of miserable\nhead colds and sinus congestion.\nPenetro Nose Drops contain ephe\ndrine (opening-up action) and other\n\u201cbalanced medication.\u201d They help\nto shrink swollen membranes,\nsoothe the inflamed area, make\nbreathing easier. 25c, 50c, $1 bottles\nat druggists. Convenient purse size,\n10c. Demand Penetro Nose Drops.\n\n\u2018Q\nZ/VQ X\nks, 7\nI3 \\_~\nTHEGREATEST o (e\nIN AMERICA L\nSAMPLE ONE-WAY FARES Your Greyhound ticket includes\n-_\u2014 such travel features as modern\nbuses driven by the world\u2019s\nHOUSTON 395 safest drivers deep-cush-\nNEW ORLEANS 9.50 Ioned. adjustable seats lib\neral stopover privileges\nAUSTIN 150 pbroad observation windows\nDALLAS 495 convenient schedules yet it\ncosts less than driving a small\nMEMPHIS ...........$11.90 car. Truly a Greyhound ticket\nST. LOUIS ...........$14.50 Is the greatest travel bargain in\u2019\nCHICAGO ..........$i750 America today.\n_GREYHOUND TERMINAL o f\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014N i\nP d N b T\nG 8 3 5 1 GREYLII_OUND\ni LEl\n;\u00e9i;\"el;;xd \"n'\ufb01stcom -pany\u00bb th\u00e9or_v\nl EN SALE On Sale Wednes-\nVALUABLE DISCOUNT CERTIFICATE w7 M\nand Friday.\nYon Must Have This Certificate in Onder to Obtain Pen\nThis certificate and 69 entitles the bearer to one of\nour Genuine Indestructible VACUUM FILLER SAC-\nLESS FOUNTAIN PENS. Visible ink supply. You\nc see the ink. c\nz Factory Lifetime Guarantee with Each Pen\n9 A\u201cF,:\u2018F\u201cA? Sizes for ladies, men, boys and girls A\u201crhlr'z\u2018.: r?_\nD SAVING! THE PEN THAT IS GUARANTEED LEAKPROOF SAVING! cC\nO\nO R A I IS T v s\n(G- g N A o\nSRR YL IR R AR S 4\n2 Copyright, 1936, A. L. 0\nTHE NEW PLUNGER FILLER\u2014VACUUM ZIP\u2014ONLY ONE PULL AND IT'S FULL 8\n\u2014J The PEN holds much more ink than any ordinary pen on the market! You can write for a month on one\nfilling! No repair bills! No lever filler! No pressure bar. Every pen tested and guaranteed to be un- o\nbreakable for life. Get yours NOW. THIS PEN GIVEN FREE if you can buy one in San Antonio for any-\nwhere near the above price. This certificate good only while advertising sale is on. Manufacturer's guaran- 2\n's\u00e9\u2018:.'it.h\u2018:.\\'i\u2019.ry.z)e:_.y\u201c,\u2018 are the Exclusive Dealers in this type of pen and it cannot be bought elsewhere in\nPrice.\n\n=3 PENCILS TO MATCH ABOVE PENS, 29\u00a2\nPOSITIVELY SOLD ONLY AT\ns ouc. SommersDrug Store No. 5]z xms o\nfor Mail Orders s Buy several of them\n(L) 2 Taene\nOpposite New Postoffice\n\nWANT ADS\u2014FANNIN 1231\nGovernment Plays\nTo Brake Slump\nNEWS BEHIND THE NEWS\n(World copyright 1937 by King Features Syndicate, Inc. All rights rese\nT amendisntinm inn 111 Ar im mart atrintlyvy nnrnhihitad\nReproduction in full or i\nWASHINGTON, Nov. 30.\u2014The\n|government is playing for this bus\niness situation to brake its own de\n|cline much sooner than previously\n{expected\u2014possibly within the next\n130 to 60 days.\nA hint of this hope (which will not\nnow be admitted publicly), lies be\nhind the latest Roosevelt move on\ngovernment purchases, He has $275,-\n000,000 to buy government supplies\nduring the next seven months. His\npurchasing agent has been instruct\ned to buy as much as possible \u201cwith\n|in the next month or two,\u201d which,\nof course, means less than normal\nbuying for the remaining five\nmonths.\nIn this instance, Dr. Roosevelt is\nobviously gambling on a turn, not\nwithin six months to a year as\npreviously indicated, but within the\nimmediate future,\nA definite and encouraging line on\nthe buying power of the people and\nits present relation to prices and\nproduction is given in the follow\ning monthly business chart. Here\nyou will see that while the people\u2019s\nincome, particularly farm income,\nhas been slipping, it has not de\ncreased as much or as fast as in\n|dustria1 production, Note well, too,\nhow fast prices have been falling,\n\u2018and the fact that they have not yet\ncaused a commensurate decrease in.\nthe cost of living (that result lags\n|a month or two, but is surely at\nhand).\nl The chart:\nNon-agri- Cash Cost of Whole- Indus.\ncultural Farm Inc. living sale Produc,\nincome farm mkt-1923-100 prices 1923-25-\n1924:29- ings 1924- 1926-100 100\n100 29-100 Seas,\nSeas, Seas. Adj.\nAdj. Adi.\nAve. 1929 1070 103.5 100.1 95.3 119\nAve. 1931 855 58.0 87.2 73.0 81\n|Ave. 1936 ...1000000 870 745 8438 808- 105\nJan, 1937 928 75.0 86.9 85.9 114\nFeb. siiiieiieiee.. 938 70.5 87.2 86.3 116\nMar. soieieeeeiene.. 953 81.5 87.9 87.8 118\nADI. tivveececsareces 962 89.0 88.3 88.0 118\n(May .iieeeeenniei., 968 78.0 88.8 87.4 118\n|June 969 84.5 88.9 87.2 114\nJUlYy cieevenennnenes 977 945 88.9 879 114\nAU e 98.2 85.0 89.0 87.5 117\nSept. ..iieveviene.. 968 81.0 89.4 874 111\nOCt, iiiiiiieaiae.., 964 775 89.5 85.4 103\n'Nov. (est.) 95.2 73.5 89.4 83.1 92\nThese and other current figures,\nn part strictly prohibited.) i 1\nprove this decline has been steeper\nand of greater magnitude than any\none predicted. But that very fact in\nitself now is encouraging the gen\neral impression that the adjustment\nstage should be reached earlier than\nexpected. Of course, the economists\ncan be wrong again.\nPolitical developments and even\nwinter weather could be offsetting\nlfactors in a situation as delicate as\nthis one. A hard winter with floods,\nfor instance, would overturn govern-\nment spending and budget calcula-l\ntions, also buying power next year.\nPolitical developments in broad per\nspective, however, seem to be on the\nencouraging side.\nThus the guessing seems to boil\ndown to as good an answer as there\nis available.\no 1\nMore conclusive evidence of\u2018\nchanging thought is displayed in the\nway his caytious economic advisers\nnow are doping out the price situa\ntion.\nTheir latest figures indicate prices\nhave been declining more rapidly\nthan expected. Metals, steel scrap,\nrubber and hides declined further\nfrom mid-October to the third week\nof November, and this drop has be\ngun, at last, to bring similar results\nin the prices of some finished in\ndustrial products. Livestock and\nmeats declined substantially, too.\nThis brought wholesale prices\ndown to 83.1 for November, the low\nest since December last year. Now,\n;no one knows how far prices must\n-a\u201cgo to meet demand, but a very good\ninside guess now is that the index\nwill probably get down to 81 or 82\nbefore the biggest bulk of arrested\nbuying is encouraged to come into\nthe market, thus stopping the de\ncline.\nThat expected point is only two or\nthree points below the existing level.\nThe guess is not a wild stab in\nthe dark. It is based on a size-up\nof existing stocks and the known\nexisting buying power of the people.\nSooner or later this demand will un\nquestionably put a bottom to the\ncurrently readjusting price situa\ntion.\nSizing-up stocks is harder than\nestimating income, but there is evi\ndence that consumption now actu\nally is larger than production in\nsteel. The steel authorities Iron\nAge, for one, are saying steel has\nhit a bottom, aft\u00e9r a sharper drop\nthan in 1929-30 depression. If steel\nfinds its footing, the sentiment of\nbusiness may be bolstered. Watch\nboth steel and autos for the tip.\nOverstocks in textiles, shoes and\nsome other lines look big now be\ncause business is bad, But, if steel\nand autos bump bojtom, these other\ninventories will at once look more\nnormal. In other words, you do not\nhave to wait until all inventories of\nall lines are cleaned out before the\nlatent buying urge is awakened.\nNotes\u2014Commerce Secretary Roper\nis still predicting Christmas busi-\nIness will be better than last year,\nbut few economists privately agree\nwith him Many current figures\nare being made to look much better\nthan they are. The favorite trick is l\nto use figures for the first nine\nmonths of the year, thus minimizing\nthe situation of the last quarter\nRecent government announcements\nindicate little increase in unemploy-\nment or relief demands. The official\nfactory payrolls figure showed an\nincrease for October, Incredible as it\nseems. Most authorities attribute\nthis to technical lags and defects in\ngathering the figures Federal\nstatisticians rechecked the payroll\nfigure because they could not be\nlieve their eyes, but they failed to\nfind an error The Ayres|\nTHE SAN ANTONIO LIGHT.\nSonja Henie Hurt\nby Movie Ice Fall\nHOLLYWOOD, Nov. 30.\u2014(\")\u2014\u2018\nSonja Henie, Norwegian skatingi\nstar, was to be X-rayed today to de\ntermine if she suffered a slight\nbrain concussion in a movie ice rink\nfall last Friday.\nThe back of her head struck the\nice after one of her skate\u00e9s slipped\non a piece of cotton. She complain\ned of dizziness on the set yesterday.\n\u2014_\u2014\u2014\nBetter used cars at prices and\nterms to fit every pocketbook list\ned in Classification 73, Light want\nads,\n\u2014_\u2014\u2014\u2014\nThe easy way to find a room,\napartment or house is through\nLight Classified rental ads.\n\nthat stock prices were too high any\nway with reference to dividends is\ngenerally accepted here Good\nsign of co-operation. The A. P. of\nL. has a line in its monthly busi\nness survey advising union mem\nbers to \u201cco-operate to cut costs by\nimproving efficiency\u201d for employers\nwho have made satisfactory collec-}\nItive bargaining arrangements.\n\u2014\ufb02Vb_FVAi\u2018_V_\u201c \u2014_ 0 0 0 VY SIS IS ISIKS) ()0 SIS\n7\nil TABLE CLOTHS (1 L LASTEX GIRDLES\nM Reg. 39c NN\n9 o X N N 2 N =N\nR e 1 7 CotamGereree 2 for 1\n8 l?:!flme(;'r 234 E. HOUSTON ST. Panty, Supporter, Bracelet Styles\n\n\nv 5\n\n\n@dl= TO MAKE IMMEDIATE ROOM FOR CHRISTMAS MERCHANDISE\nX TING\nBLANKETS VAL. TO 89 |OU GOWNS\nReg. Extra Sizes\nol P size 700 gt sd\nul Poc..., _ Black Plaids 89\u00a2 VALUES 4\nt 4 W Soft, Fleecy and Warm k\n2| Loy it Quaniy Sl s el\nM \\%f:\\;\\ i Colors: for V\u2018::\u2019elllht(;'immed and FOR\no -_\u2014 S Rose\u2014Blue nished.\nT i Green\u2014Orchid Specially Priced for Drastic Clearance\nk S and Gold\nal WOMEN'S PURE SILK HOSE\n=l INDIAN BLANKETS VAL. TO $1.59\no c 4 $\u2018I\n0 PAIR\no\nB AT H R 0 B E s 'voi e, REGULAR 39\